BryanCutler commented on a change in pull request #2698: ARROW-3428: [Python] Fix from_pandas conversion from float to bool
URL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/2698#discussion_r224854127



 ##########
 File path: cpp/src/arrow/python/numpy_to_arrow.cc
 ##########
 @@ -424,38 +451,12 @@ inline Status NumPyConverter::ConvertData(std::shared_ptr<Buffer>* data) {
   return Status::OK();
 }

-template <>
-inline Status NumPyConverter::ConvertData<BooleanType>(std::shared_ptr<Buffer>* data) {
-  int64_t nbytes = BitUtil::BytesForBits(length_);
-  std::shared_ptr<Buffer> buffer;
-  RETURN_NOT_OK(AllocateBuffer(pool_, nbytes, &buffer));
-
-  Ndarray1DIndexer<uint8_t> values(arr_);

 Review comment:
   The output array is visited and there is no check for the dtype except in the spec`ConvertData` specialized for date types.  In the case of a boolean output type, it assumed the numpy data was `unit8_t`.  In the other cases, the dtype is sent to the `CastBuffer` where the input and output types are parameterized, but it expects the buffer to be in Arrow layout, so for bools it needs to be converted to a bitmask before.

